{{Quote|That may very well be an emergency data pod from the Death Star. Retrieve it.|[[Tyber Zann]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Empire at War: Forces of Corruption">''[[Star Wars: Empire at War: Forces of Corruption]]''</ref>}}
'''Data pods''' were small pods used to store important information.

Data pods were used as backup surveillance devices by the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]], to be ejected from a vessel under attack. A [[C-9979 landing craft/Legends|C-9979 landing craft]] launched its data pods during a battle against [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Adi Gallia/Legends|Adi Gallia]] and [[Reti]] of the [[Lok Revenants/Legends|Lok Revenants]] in the [[Ruby Nebula]]. Adi and Reti were able to destroy the pods, containing their ship IDs, in addition to the lander itself.

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], it was standard [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] procedure to eject data pods from a ship during an emergency, as was the case when the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|first Death Star]] was [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|destroyed]]. The [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Tyber Zann]] scoured the wreckage of the Death Star for these data pods shortly afterward. In them, he discovered the blueprints of the [[Aggressor-class destroyer|''Aggressor''-class Star Destroyer]] and information on the [[Eclipse (Eclipse-class)|''Eclipse'']].

